?f_ri=2732296", "dom_id": "work_41157204", "summary": "CREATIVE TRANSLATION: THE CASE OF MALAY PANTUN\nThe subject of the present analysis is the creativity of translation within the translation of Malay pantun-a poetic form which has aroused considerable fascination on the part of Western researchers for several centuries. For pantun is something more than merely a four-line verse with an abab rhyme; an exemplification of the present thesis being two examples of pantun in the translation of Robert Stiller. Resumen: El tema del presente an\u00e1lisis trata sobre la creatividad de la traducci\u00f3n to-mando como ejemplo el pantun malayo, una forma po\u00e9tica que desde hace siglos ejerce una enorme fascinaci\u00f3n en los investigadores occidentales. El pantun es algo m\u00e1s que un simple cuarteto con una estructura de rimas abab. Un ejemplo de la tesis presentada son dos pantunes en traducci\u00f3n de Robert Stiller. Palabras clave: traducci\u00f3n creativa, pantun malayo, Robert Stiller.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 61400167, "asset_id": 41157204, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 137360384, "first_name": "Tadeusz", "last_name": "Szczerbowski", "domain_name": "ledson", "page_name": "TadeuszSzczerbowski", "display_name": "Tadeusz Szczerbowski", "profile_url": "https://ledson.academia.edu/TadeuszSzczerbowski?f_ri=2732296", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/137360384/37091214/31514175/s65_tadeusz.szczerbowski.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 1751, "name": "Creativity", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Creativity?f_ri=2732296", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 43424, "name": "Pantun", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pantun?f_ri=2732296", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 50804, "name": "Literary translation", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Literary_translation?f_ri=2732296", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 586820, "name": "Malay Culture", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Culture?f_ri=2732296", "nofollow": false}, {"id": 2732296, "name": "Malay pantun", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_pantun?f_ri=2732296"}]}, {"id": 50993861, "title": "The Malay Language \u2018Pantun\u2019 of Melaka Chetti Indians in Malaysia: Malay Worldview, Lived Experiences and Hybrid Identity", "created_at": "2021-08-24T08:19:02.325-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/50993861/The_Malay_Language_Pantun_of_Melaka_Chetti_Indians_in_Malaysia_Malay_Worldview_Lived_Experiences_and_Hybrid_Identity?f_ri=2732296", "dom_id": "work_50993861", "summary": "The Melaka Chetti Indians are a small community of \u2018peranakan\u2019 (Malay meaning \u2018locally born\u2019) people in Malaysia. The Melaka Chettis are descendants of traders from the Indian subcontinent who married local women, mostly during the time of the Melaka Malay Empire from the 1400s to 1500s. The Melaka Chettis adopted the local lingua franca \u2018bahasa Melayu\u2019 or Malay as their first language together with the \u2018adat\u2019 (Malay meaning \u2018customs\u2019) of the Malay people, their traditional mannerisms and also their literary prowess. Not only did the Melaka Chettis successfully adopted the literary traditions of the Malay people, they also adapted these arts forms to become part of their own unique hybrid identities based on their worldviews and lived experiences within the Malay Peninsula or more famously known as the Golden Chersonese / Khersonese. Based on our one year plus fieldwork in \u2018Kampung Chetti\u2019 or Chetti Village in the state of Melaka, Malaysia where we carried out extensive oral history...", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 68865103, "asset_id": 50993861, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 54821723, "first_name": "Indrani", "last_name": "Pillay", "domain_name": "independent", "page_name": "IndraniPillay", "display_name": "Indrani Pillay", "profile_url": "https://independent.a